NAMING CONVENTION:

  SEMANTIC PREFIXES:

    g####_* - user routines of a particular data structure
        (# - lowercase identifier of a data structure, from 3 to 5 chars, first
        letter is consonant)
    ig####_* - internal routines of a particular data structure
        (# - lowercase identifier of a data structure, from 3 to 5 chars, first
        letter is consonant)
    gena_* - user library routines
    igena_* - internal library routines
    __* - local and/or temporary names (e.g. in struct typedefs)
    _impl_* - wrapped routine
    tp* - template parameter (rest must be in CamelCase, e.g. tpVecName)

  VARIABLE SUFFIXES:

    *_c - const

  ARGUMENT PREFIXES:

    p* - handle passed by pointer
    ptr_* - argument is a pointer (for macros arguments ONLY!)
    OUT_* - pointer to an output value

  TYPE SUFFIXES:

    *_e - enum
    *_s - struct
    *_p - pointer
    *_t - handle type / type alias
    *_ptr - handle pointer
    *_s_typedef - for struct names in typedefs

  NOTES:

    1. Names of the defines and macros must be uppercase.
